1
00:00:00,086 --> 00:00:01,567
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,567 --> 00:00:03,100
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,567 --> 00:00:04,834
I said stop, Han Ji Hun!

4
00:00:04,836 --> 00:00:05,836
Thief!

5
00:00:05,838 --> 00:00:07,905
He's a thief!

6
00:00:09,071 --> 00:00:10,071
Stop right there!

7
00:00:16,718 --> 00:00:17,718
Seriously.

8
00:00:21,198 --> 00:00:23,798
We should talk. Why did you run away?

9
00:00:23,938 --> 00:00:26,438
When did I ever run away?

10
00:00:27,016 --> 00:00:28,816
Hey, let go so we can talk, okay?

11
00:00:28,818 --> 00:00:30,485
I saw the article. What happened?

12
00:00:31,582 --> 00:00:33,285
Can we go somewhere quieter and talk?

13
00:00:33,285 --> 00:00:34,285
Answer me, now!

14
00:00:34,824 --> 00:00:35,958
What was that confession the other day?

15
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:37,924
And what was that kiss supposed to mean?

16
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:40,618
I'll tell you everything.

17
00:00:40,671 --> 00:00:41,671
Excuse me.

18
00:00:42,318 --> 00:00:43,318
Well...

19
00:00:43,871 --> 00:00:46,305
So, just let go first...

20
00:00:48,331 --> 00:00:49,331
Hey, Han Ji Hun!

21
00:00:54,912 --> 00:00:55,912
Darn it.

22
00:00:58,002 --> 00:00:59,785
You said we'd talk.
Why are you running again?

23
00:00:59,895 --> 00:01:01,618
Because you're losing it.

24
00:01:01,618 --> 00:01:03,418
How can I stay calm right now?

25
00:01:03,642 --> 00:01:05,518
How can I be in my right mind?

26
00:01:05,518 --> 00:01:08,218
Then get a hold of yourself first.

27
00:01:08,218 --> 00:01:09,218
Seriously.

28
00:01:09,771 --> 00:01:11,104
What do you think you're doing?

29
00:01:13,371 --> 00:01:16,471
Sorry. Let's talk later, okay?

30
00:01:18,437 --> 00:01:19,804
Stop right there!

31
00:01:26,635 --> 00:01:27,685
What are you doing? Let go.

32
00:01:27,818 --> 00:01:28,984
Hand over my wallet first.

33
00:01:28,986 --> 00:01:30,120
Your wallet? What wallet?

34
00:01:30,657 --> 00:01:32,657
You're working together, aren't you?
Hand it over.

35
00:01:32,771 --> 00:01:34,171
Don't make a scene.

36
00:01:34,731 --> 00:01:36,331
I lost him because of you! Darn it.

37
00:01:38,962 --> 00:01:40,083
There's no cash in the wallet,

38
00:01:40,252 --> 00:01:42,351
and I'll cancel the cards,
so you won't be able to use them.

39
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:44,860
It's a luxury wallet,
but I've used it for over ten years,

40
00:01:44,862 --> 00:01:46,185
so it won't help your household much.

41
00:01:46,745 --> 00:01:47,945
Just hand it over.

42
00:01:48,685 --> 00:01:50,085
What a lunatic.

43
00:01:50,265 --> 00:01:51,265
Let go!

44
00:01:51,984 --> 00:01:52,984
What in the world?

45
00:02:01,645 --> 00:02:02,645
Gyeol.

46
00:02:03,685 --> 00:02:04,685
Long time no see.

47
00:02:05,264 --> 00:02:06,331
It must've been a long trip.

48
00:02:06,565 --> 00:02:09,298
Mr. Seo, you didn't have to come
all the way here.

49
00:02:10,071 --> 00:02:12,438
The Chairman wanted to see you right away,
so he sent a car.

50
00:02:12,858 --> 00:02:14,158
I came with Mr. Ju.

51
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:17,091
Okay. How's Grandpa?

52
00:02:17,857 --> 00:02:19,124
He's holding up for now.

53
00:02:20,305 --> 00:02:22,205
Let's go. The Chairman is waiting.

54
00:02:22,685 --> 00:02:23,685
Okay.

55
00:02:37,151 --> 00:02:38,185
Gyeol!

56
00:02:38,848 --> 00:02:40,418
Have you been well, Mr. Ju?

57
00:02:40,551 --> 00:02:41,918
Same as always.

58
00:02:42,931 --> 00:02:44,014
Is that all your luggage?

59
00:02:44,117 --> 00:02:45,617
It's fine. I'll do it.

60
00:03:04,244 --> 00:03:06,078
Why is this happening to me?

61
00:03:07,211 --> 00:03:08,744
Just why?

62
00:04:00,598 --> 00:04:01,598
What is that?

63
00:04:02,091 --> 00:04:03,391
Chaga mushrooms.

64
00:04:04,271 --> 00:04:06,637
I heard they're good for cancer patients.

65
00:04:07,278 --> 00:04:08,644
You're taking them to the Chairman?

66
00:04:09,051 --> 00:04:10,051
Yes.

67
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:14,549
By the way,
your dad told me not to go there again.

68
00:04:14,551 --> 00:04:17,005
If I go, he'll be furious, right?

69
00:04:18,405 --> 00:04:21,105
But it doesn't feel right
to send this by delivery.

70
00:04:22,912 --> 00:04:23,979
Should I take it for you?

71
00:04:24,372 --> 00:04:26,372
You? What's gotten into you?

72
00:04:26,818 --> 00:04:29,351
You used to hate me even going there.

73
00:04:29,985 --> 00:04:31,651
The Chairman is ill.

74
00:04:31,798 --> 00:04:33,398
It's only right
that I visit him at least once.

75
00:04:35,565 --> 00:04:38,431
I guess you were worried about me
after all,

76
00:04:39,657 --> 00:04:42,124
seeing how you wrapped things up
and came so quickly.

77
00:04:42,398 --> 00:04:43,398
How are you feeling?

78
00:04:43,972 --> 00:04:45,805
As you can see, I'm full of energy.

79
00:04:47,418 --> 00:04:49,818
Are you disappointed I look fine?

80
00:04:50,398 --> 00:04:53,598
I heard from Mr. Seo.
Why did you give up treatment?

81
00:04:54,397 --> 00:04:56,064
Treatment, my foot.

82
00:04:57,137 --> 00:04:59,004
If it could be cured, I would've taken it.

83
00:04:59,651 --> 00:05:00,651
Grandpa.

84
00:05:03,045 --> 00:05:04,312
It's too early, you brat.

85
00:05:05,031 --> 00:05:06,331
Save your tears...

86
00:05:07,324 --> 00:05:09,824
for after I'm gone,
in front of my portrait.

87
00:05:11,105 --> 00:05:13,538
Don't be like that.
Come to the hospital with me tomorrow.

88
00:05:13,985 --> 00:05:16,318
If we look for it,
I'm sure we'll find a way.

89
00:05:18,319 --> 00:05:21,619
While I'm still clear-headed,

90
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,757
there's something I need to finish.

91
00:05:26,358 --> 00:05:27,958
Until I do,

92
00:05:29,331 --> 00:05:31,098
I won't be able to close my eyes.

93
00:05:33,255 --> 00:05:34,322
Don't say any more.

94
00:05:34,722 --> 00:05:36,789
Something? What do you mean?

95
00:05:37,242 --> 00:05:41,042
What's the rush?
You'll hear everything in time.

96
00:05:43,655 --> 00:05:46,089
What are they talking about
that's taking so long?

97
00:05:46,855 --> 00:05:50,422
Well, it's been almost ten years.
They must have a lot to say.

98
00:05:50,536 --> 00:05:53,136
What a grand homecoming.

99
00:05:54,089 --> 00:05:57,122
Have you been well, Mother, Father?

100
00:05:57,722 --> 00:05:59,689
Of course we have.

101
00:06:00,022 --> 00:06:01,455
- Sit down.
- Yes.

102
00:06:01,622 --> 00:06:02,622
All right.

103
00:06:03,722 --> 00:06:07,859
It's been a while.
So, are you staying for good?

104
00:06:07,943 --> 00:06:09,876
No, not really.

105
00:06:09,955 --> 00:06:12,622
No? Then are you just visiting?

106
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:13,731
Yes.

107
00:06:13,815 --> 00:06:15,469
Right, that's good.

108
00:06:15,495 --> 00:06:17,695
You shouldn't throw away
the career you built there.

109
00:06:18,289 --> 00:06:22,071
And that award you got,
not just anyone can get that.

110
00:06:22,155 --> 00:06:24,489
You are really impressive.

111
00:06:25,422 --> 00:06:27,105
What did Grandpa say?

112
00:06:27,189 --> 00:06:29,155
What did you talk about for so long?

113
00:06:29,288 --> 00:06:31,255
Nothing much. Just this and that.

114
00:06:31,729 --> 00:06:34,095
By the way, where's Min Ho?

115
00:06:34,589 --> 00:06:36,589
He went out to play golf.
He should be back soon.

116
00:06:37,922 --> 00:06:41,222
But actually, I'm a bit disappointed.

117
00:06:41,689 --> 00:06:42,722
- Sorry?
- That award you got,

118
00:06:42,722 --> 00:06:44,505
and even your return.

119
00:06:44,589 --> 00:06:46,926
I had to hear it all through Mr. Seo.

120
00:06:46,928 --> 00:06:49,261
I'm still your father, aren't I?

121
00:06:50,522 --> 00:06:51,522
I'm sorry.

122
00:06:51,789 --> 00:06:54,068
There's a saying,
"You should never take in"...

123
00:06:55,555 --> 00:06:57,489
Honey, what are you saying?

124
00:07:13,843 --> 00:07:14,843
Seo Seung Ri.

125
00:07:15,722 --> 00:07:16,871
What brings you here?

126
00:07:16,955 --> 00:07:19,189
- I came on an errand for Mom.
- An errand?

127
00:07:20,155 --> 00:07:22,255
Nothing else?

128
00:07:23,922 --> 00:07:24,922
There you go again.

129
00:07:25,396 --> 00:07:27,696
You scare me the most
when you make that face.

130
00:07:28,982 --> 00:07:31,015
Come on, let's go in.

131
00:07:32,955 --> 00:07:34,589
Hey, that watch...

132
00:07:43,322 --> 00:07:45,122
- I'm back.
- Hey, come on in.

133
00:07:47,022 --> 00:07:49,322
- You're back?
- Yeah, how have you been?

134
00:07:50,155 --> 00:07:51,155
Same as always.

135
00:07:51,322 --> 00:07:52,855
Hello, sir and ma'am.

136
00:07:53,155 --> 00:07:54,522
Welcome, Ms. Seo.

137
00:07:54,989 --> 00:07:56,655
How come you two came together?

138
00:07:57,255 --> 00:07:58,922
We just ran into each other at the gate.

139
00:08:00,722 --> 00:08:03,089
My goodness, isn't that Seung Ri?

140
00:08:03,722 --> 00:08:05,371
Why haven't you come by lately?

141
00:08:05,455 --> 00:08:07,155
I'm sorry. I've been busy.

142
00:08:07,722 --> 00:08:09,855
My mom sent this for the Chairman.

143
00:08:10,142 --> 00:08:12,075
They're chaga mushrooms.
She said they're good when brewed.

144
00:08:12,355 --> 00:08:14,318
She shouldn't have.

145
00:08:14,402 --> 00:08:16,435
Please thank your mother for me.

146
00:08:17,075 --> 00:08:18,075
Yes.

147
00:08:20,489 --> 00:08:21,489
Good to see you, Seung Ri.

148
00:08:21,755 --> 00:08:24,155
I've been hearing about you
through Mr. Seo.

149
00:08:24,989 --> 00:08:25,989
Really?

150
00:08:26,322 --> 00:08:29,222
I'm a bit late,
but congratulations on your award.

151
00:08:29,222 --> 00:08:31,689
You don't have to congratulate me,
but thanks.

152
00:08:34,235 --> 00:08:36,702
You should stay for a while.

153
00:08:37,188 --> 00:08:38,322
Have dinner before you go.

154
00:08:38,415 --> 00:08:40,915
You can see the Chairman when he wakes up.

155
00:08:45,622 --> 00:08:47,855
What are you doing? Come sit.

156
00:08:49,455 --> 00:08:50,455
Yes.

157
00:08:57,381 --> 00:08:59,889
You two always made such a good pair,
even when you were young.

158
00:08:59,889 --> 00:09:01,251
You still look good together.

159
00:09:01,589 --> 00:09:04,122
Mother, what are you saying?

160
00:09:04,689 --> 00:09:08,622
What? Didn't they like each other
since high school?

161
00:09:11,249 --> 00:09:12,971
We'll give you some space...

162
00:09:13,055 --> 00:09:14,655
so you can talk.

163
00:09:18,989 --> 00:09:21,255
Why are you still sitting here
without a clue?

164
00:09:21,755 --> 00:09:24,118
Go upstairs and let them talk.

165
00:09:24,202 --> 00:09:25,368
Mother, please.

166
00:09:27,543 --> 00:09:29,743
I should get going. See you next time.

167
00:09:29,855 --> 00:09:30,855
All right.

168
00:09:31,242 --> 00:09:33,842
I'll visit your house next time
to greet your mother as well.

169
00:09:34,222 --> 00:09:35,289
Okay, Gyeol.

170
00:09:37,122 --> 00:09:38,722
I'll take my leave, Director.

171
00:09:41,589 --> 00:09:43,322
How come he gets called by his name,
but I'm "Director?"

172
00:09:43,406 --> 00:09:44,789
This isn't even the office.

173
00:09:45,396 --> 00:09:48,362
Why did he even come?
Who said he was welcome?

174
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:50,689
He said he's only here briefly.

175
00:09:50,976 --> 00:09:52,509
And you believe that?

176
00:09:53,389 --> 00:09:54,822
What are you trying to say?

177
00:09:54,822 --> 00:09:57,222
I heard Father called in Lawyer Kang.

178
00:09:57,222 --> 00:09:58,755
- So what?
- You don't know?

179
00:09:59,389 --> 00:10:01,022
In the end, yours and Min Ho's shares...

180
00:10:01,022 --> 00:10:03,201
Please, stop overreacting.

181
00:10:03,223 --> 00:10:05,223
He's already well established over there.

182
00:10:06,255 --> 00:10:08,189
Why do you think he became an architect?

183
00:10:08,275 --> 00:10:10,975
Do you really think
it's just because he likes architecture?

184
00:10:11,422 --> 00:10:13,855
Eun Su Jeong, my crystal.

185
00:10:14,408 --> 00:10:17,508
You're great, but you're too transparent.

186
00:10:18,489 --> 00:10:21,989
Everything you think shows on your face.
That's the problem.

187
00:10:24,035 --> 00:10:25,701
Why do you think I'm called "Su Jeong?"

188
00:10:26,322 --> 00:10:28,022
Because I'm clear and sparkling.

189
00:10:31,355 --> 00:10:33,822
So why is that a problem?

190
00:10:35,142 --> 00:10:36,675
I wonder why.

191
00:10:48,922 --> 00:10:51,155
I never planned to come back...

192
00:10:54,089 --> 00:10:55,155
but here I am again.

193
00:11:10,789 --> 00:11:15,389
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

194
00:11:15,782 --> 00:11:18,522
<i>Happy birthday, my dear son</i>

195
00:11:18,909 --> 00:11:21,209
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

196
00:11:21,422 --> 00:11:22,889
(Han Gyeol! Happy birthday!)

197
00:11:22,889 --> 00:11:25,455
Wait. Make a wish
before you blow out the candles.

198
00:11:35,989 --> 00:11:36,989
What did you wish for?

199
00:11:37,155 --> 00:11:40,722
For you and me to live happily together
for a long time.

200
00:11:41,426 --> 00:11:43,226
Until the end of the world.

201
00:11:43,255 --> 00:11:45,089
What? My goodness.

202
00:11:45,489 --> 00:11:49,189
Thanks to your wish,
I'm going to live a very long time.

203
00:11:50,349 --> 00:11:51,683
Here.

204
00:11:53,029 --> 00:11:54,029
Your present.

205
00:11:55,889 --> 00:11:56,722
(Real Walkie-Talkie)

206
00:11:56,769 --> 00:12:00,369
It's a walkie-talkie! I really wanted one!

207
00:12:04,055 --> 00:12:05,055
Excuse me.

208
00:12:06,455 --> 00:12:08,155
Could you take a photo of us?

209
00:12:11,355 --> 00:12:12,355
Sure.

210
00:12:19,289 --> 00:12:21,222
- Here goes.
- Smile.

211
00:12:21,222 --> 00:12:22,589
One, two, three.

212
00:12:40,855 --> 00:12:41,855
Yes?

213
00:12:43,089 --> 00:12:44,789
You caught the pickpocket?

214
00:12:46,755 --> 00:12:48,755
What? A foreigner?

215
00:12:49,322 --> 00:12:50,955
Not a Korean man and woman duo?

216
00:12:52,455 --> 00:12:54,989
Okay, I'll come pick it up.

217
00:13:02,622 --> 00:13:03,822
What are you doing? Let go.

218
00:13:05,889 --> 00:13:06,955
I made a big mistake.

219
00:13:13,555 --> 00:13:14,889
Lucky Joy?

220
00:13:15,555 --> 00:13:18,055
What? He ran away?

221
00:13:19,655 --> 00:13:21,789
He should be on his knees begging.

222
00:13:24,189 --> 00:13:25,789
What a terrible guy.

223
00:13:27,055 --> 00:13:30,889
Even when I was waiting at the airport,
I still had a bit of hope.

224
00:13:31,789 --> 00:13:33,955
I hoped it wasn't true,
that it was all a misunderstanding.

225
00:13:34,889 --> 00:13:36,989
I wanted so badly
to hear him say it was all a mistake.

226
00:13:38,714 --> 00:13:40,788
You were foolish to hope.

227
00:13:41,589 --> 00:13:43,989
He ended your lease behind your back,
changed the server password,

228
00:13:44,501 --> 00:13:47,222
and there's even an acquisition article.
It's over.

229
00:13:49,369 --> 00:13:50,869
Why am I like this?

230
00:13:51,682 --> 00:13:52,949
Mom was right.

231
00:13:53,389 --> 00:13:54,855
No matter what I do, I mess everything up.

232
00:13:55,828 --> 00:13:57,822
I must really be an idiot.

233
00:13:57,822 --> 00:13:59,922
You're not an idiot.

234
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:02,122
He's the one who tricked you on purpose.

235
00:14:02,762 --> 00:14:05,095
At least when he kissed me,

236
00:14:05,522 --> 00:14:08,622
I should've known if he meant it or not.

237
00:14:08,622 --> 00:14:10,389
Don't do that!

238
00:14:11,955 --> 00:14:15,289
You should get a grip now
and figure out what to do.

239
00:14:17,455 --> 00:14:20,255
I don't know.
I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.

240
00:14:21,222 --> 00:14:23,022
I can't think straight.

241
00:14:24,155 --> 00:14:28,155
You're not going to just give up
on Joy like this, are you?

242
00:14:29,275 --> 00:14:32,275
How could I? Joy is like my child.

243
00:14:33,155 --> 00:14:34,495
It's my baby...

244
00:14:34,579 --> 00:14:36,889
that I raised and finally brought
into the world.

245
00:14:41,788 --> 00:14:43,422
What on earth are you talking about?

246
00:14:44,315 --> 00:14:46,848
Eun Ae, did you have a secret child?

247
00:14:47,989 --> 00:14:48,989
What?

248
00:14:54,562 --> 00:14:58,162
<i>- Congratulations
- Congratulations</i>

249
00:14:58,162 --> 00:15:00,762
<i>- Congratulations
- Congratulations</i>

250
00:15:04,462 --> 00:15:05,595
What is all this?

251
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:08,121
Just blow out the candles.
They're melting.

252
00:15:08,595 --> 00:15:11,762
At least let me know
what I'm being congratulated for.

253
00:15:21,682 --> 00:15:23,782
My daughter, you've worked so hard.

254
00:15:24,426 --> 00:15:26,193
Congratulations on securing
the investment.

255
00:15:26,422 --> 00:15:29,429
Cho Eun Ae is no longer single!

256
00:15:29,515 --> 00:15:30,515
Congrats!

257
00:15:31,289 --> 00:15:32,956
Congratulations on everything.

258
00:15:34,348 --> 00:15:36,681
What? Why are you about to cry over this?

259
00:15:37,595 --> 00:15:39,029
- Let's sit.
- Sit.

260
00:15:40,962 --> 00:15:42,328
It's your day off. Where did you go?

261
00:15:43,328 --> 00:15:44,962
I thought you were sleeping in,
so I didn't wake you.

262
00:15:44,962 --> 00:15:46,528
But when I checked at lunch,
you weren't there.

263
00:15:47,362 --> 00:15:49,462
You must've gone on a date,
using work as an excuse.

264
00:15:49,588 --> 00:15:51,688
Just the two of you,
all cozy in that little room.

265
00:15:52,828 --> 00:15:54,928
Make sure to bring him home next week.

266
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:57,855
Like your dad said,
you've known him for so long.

267
00:15:57,902 --> 00:15:59,302
He must be decent.

268
00:16:01,401 --> 00:16:03,368
All right. Let's cut the cake.

269
00:16:03,862 --> 00:16:06,795
Wait. Mom, Dad...

270
00:16:09,028 --> 00:16:10,895
I have something to tell you.

271
00:16:16,562 --> 00:16:20,362
We broke up.

272
00:16:23,481 --> 00:16:24,481
What?

273
00:16:24,762 --> 00:16:26,362
You broke up?

274
00:16:27,562 --> 00:16:29,095
What do you mean?

275
00:16:29,948 --> 00:16:31,315
You just started dating.

276
00:16:31,895 --> 00:16:34,795
Did something happen? Why all of a sudden?

277
00:16:37,341 --> 00:16:39,975
I knew something felt off.

278
00:16:42,248 --> 00:16:43,615
Tell me what happened.

279
00:16:45,895 --> 00:16:46,928
Now.

280
00:16:48,881 --> 00:16:50,981
I'm sorry. I'll go upstairs.

281
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:55,695
Hey, Cho Eun Ae!

282
00:16:56,187 --> 00:16:57,221
Just let her be.

283
00:16:58,928 --> 00:17:01,262
Ask her later, slowly.

284
00:17:02,154 --> 00:17:04,421
What? She got dumped already?

285
00:17:16,228 --> 00:17:17,228
Joy.

286
00:17:19,662 --> 00:17:20,762
What should I do?

287
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:25,367
What am I supposed to do now?

288
00:17:25,975 --> 00:17:28,442
I couldn't understand your question.

289
00:17:29,055 --> 00:17:30,521
It's all over. Everything!

290
00:17:37,528 --> 00:17:38,961
This isn't a lucky charm.

291
00:17:59,339 --> 00:18:00,339
Mom!

292
00:18:00,746 --> 00:18:01,746
Bit Na!

293
00:18:02,599 --> 00:18:04,332
- Were you good?
- Yeah.

294
00:18:04,332 --> 00:18:06,287
Welcome home, honey. You worked hard.

295
00:18:06,371 --> 00:18:08,573
You must be hungry. Go change and wash up.

296
00:18:08,657 --> 00:18:09,811
Okay.

297
00:18:09,885 --> 00:18:12,541
Honey, do you have time next weekend?

298
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:14,565
- For what?
- A junior of mine is getting married.

299
00:18:14,649 --> 00:18:16,124
They invited couples.

300
00:18:16,231 --> 00:18:17,764
Next weekend?

301
00:18:18,105 --> 00:18:19,855
Yeah, sure. I'm fine with it.

302
00:18:19,939 --> 00:18:22,941
About that... Can we talk?

303
00:18:23,025 --> 00:18:25,159
- Bit Na, wait a second.
- Okay.

304
00:18:27,775 --> 00:18:28,975
What do you mean?

305
00:18:29,059 --> 00:18:31,128
I shouldn't say that I'm an adjunct?

306
00:18:31,212 --> 00:18:34,101
I told my colleagues
you're a full-time professor.

307
00:18:34,185 --> 00:18:36,551
We have to keep the story straight.

308
00:18:37,185 --> 00:18:41,026
But saying something that isn't true
as if it is...

309
00:18:43,486 --> 00:18:45,480
Do we really have to lie?

310
00:18:45,634 --> 00:18:47,268
How is that a lie?

311
00:18:47,340 --> 00:18:49,374
You're going to become
a full-time professor soon anyway.

312
00:18:49,578 --> 00:18:51,694
Didn't the department head say
it'll certainly happen next semester?

313
00:18:51,778 --> 00:18:54,948
That just means it's likely,
not confirmed.

314
00:18:55,032 --> 00:18:56,918
- And...
- Just help me out.

315
00:18:56,998 --> 00:18:58,748
She's much younger than me,

316
00:18:58,832 --> 00:19:01,652
and she's moving into a big apartment
in Gangnam after her wedding.

317
00:19:01,736 --> 00:19:04,552
Her husband is a plastic surgeon.

318
00:19:04,636 --> 00:19:07,336
Honey, can their apartment size and job...

319
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:09,524
really define our happiness?

320
00:19:09,618 --> 00:19:12,221
Maybe not define it, but...

321
00:19:12,305 --> 00:19:14,986
Schopenhauer argued...

322
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:19,101
that most of what we have exists
for others' eyes.

323
00:19:19,185 --> 00:19:21,889
Money and status are just illusions.

324
00:19:21,969 --> 00:19:23,522
- The essence is...
- Here we go again.

325
00:19:23,556 --> 00:19:25,390
Starting with philosophy again?

326
00:19:25,474 --> 00:19:29,052
Just think of it as boosting
your wife's pride in front of her juniors.

327
00:19:29,136 --> 00:19:31,847
Okay, I'll go.

328
00:19:31,887 --> 00:19:34,230
But I won't say I'm full-time myself.

329
00:19:34,314 --> 00:19:36,714
You don't have to.
Everyone already thinks so.

330
00:19:37,607 --> 00:19:40,040
This is the shirt you'll wear that day.

331
00:19:40,825 --> 00:19:42,992
It was on sale at the duty-free shop.

332
00:19:44,052 --> 00:19:46,358
Do I embarrass you?

333
00:19:46,472 --> 00:19:48,206
Is that why you're trying to dress me up?

334
00:19:48,208 --> 00:19:51,828
Why are you reading so much
into one shirt?

335
00:19:51,912 --> 00:19:53,192
Do you think people live like you,

336
00:19:53,276 --> 00:19:55,018
looking at what's inside?

337
00:19:55,102 --> 00:19:57,824
No, they judge by appearances.

338
00:20:03,263 --> 00:20:05,421
Mom, Dad, are you arguing?

339
00:20:05,514 --> 00:20:07,414
No, we are not arguing.

340
00:20:08,228 --> 00:20:09,728
Thank you.

341
00:20:09,812 --> 00:20:12,294
Since you put in so much effort,
I'll gladly play along.

342
00:20:12,896 --> 00:20:14,061
Let's go, honey.

343
00:20:14,148 --> 00:20:16,311
Bit Na waited to eat until you came home.

344
00:20:16,395 --> 00:20:18,429
Go ahead first. I need to get changed.

345
00:20:19,501 --> 00:20:21,501
Hurry up.
We're having soft tofu stew tonight.

346
00:20:21,585 --> 00:20:23,318
Let's go.

347
00:20:35,265 --> 00:20:36,298
What is this?

348
00:20:36,972 --> 00:20:41,072
Why do ideas pour out
only when I'm at a cafe?

349
00:20:43,165 --> 00:20:46,131
Okay, I'll shower first.

350
00:20:54,791 --> 00:20:56,124
I said to come out and eat...

351
00:20:59,025 --> 00:21:01,258
Is this a room or a pigsty?

352
00:21:02,098 --> 00:21:03,231
Seriously.

353
00:21:05,718 --> 00:21:07,452
What is all this?

354
00:21:07,998 --> 00:21:10,165
He'll be the death of me.

355
00:21:10,698 --> 00:21:12,264
This brat.

356
00:21:15,231 --> 00:21:17,818
All right. Let's really get started.

357
00:21:20,031 --> 00:21:21,031
What?

358
00:21:22,484 --> 00:21:23,484
What?

359
00:21:24,165 --> 00:21:25,165
Where did they go?

360
00:21:25,665 --> 00:21:27,098
My napkins.

361
00:21:28,357 --> 00:21:30,331
My treasure!

362
00:21:32,971 --> 00:21:34,505
Mom!

363
00:21:36,744 --> 00:21:37,744
Mom!

364
00:21:38,365 --> 00:21:41,731
My treasure. No, my napkins.
Did you throw them out?

365
00:21:42,065 --> 00:21:43,731
Yeah, I did. Why?

366
00:21:44,498 --> 00:21:47,065
Am I raising a son or a pig?

367
00:21:47,338 --> 00:21:48,498
Look at your room.

368
00:21:49,278 --> 00:21:50,731
Where did you put them?

369
00:21:51,218 --> 00:21:52,785
Where did you put them?

370
00:21:52,865 --> 00:21:55,431
This brat. I just threw them in the trash!

371
00:21:55,997 --> 00:21:57,711
Seriously.

372
00:21:59,765 --> 00:22:00,898
Where did they go?

373
00:22:03,398 --> 00:22:04,431
Seriously.

374
00:22:07,565 --> 00:22:09,254
Where are they?

375
00:22:09,338 --> 00:22:11,014
Seo Seung Wu, what are you doing here?

376
00:22:11,098 --> 00:22:12,265
Why did you hit me?

377
00:22:13,065 --> 00:22:15,065
Can't you see? I'm looking for treasure.

378
00:22:16,765 --> 00:22:19,155
Where's my treasure?

379
00:22:20,737 --> 00:22:23,670
What kind of treasure are you looking for
in the trash?

380
00:22:23,698 --> 00:22:25,931
Yes, I found them!

381
00:22:26,865 --> 00:22:28,565
My golden egg.

382
00:22:29,598 --> 00:22:31,898
Are you protesting for a new tablet?

383
00:22:32,272 --> 00:22:33,472
You have a perfectly good computer...

384
00:22:35,065 --> 00:22:38,631
Someone with a salary job like you
would never understand...

385
00:22:38,885 --> 00:22:41,551
the traces of a genius artist's
inspiration and struggle.

386
00:22:43,618 --> 00:22:44,751
Look.

387
00:22:45,331 --> 00:22:47,165
Get that away from me. It stinks.

388
00:22:47,165 --> 00:22:48,598
Just look.

389
00:22:48,598 --> 00:22:49,924
Move it away.

390
00:22:49,926 --> 00:22:51,464
- You want to get hit again?
- Stop it!

391
00:22:51,466 --> 00:22:52,811
- Hey!
- Stop hitting me!

392
00:22:52,813 --> 00:22:53,865
Stop it already!

393
00:22:53,964 --> 00:22:55,097
- Hey!
- Don't follow me!

394
00:22:58,831 --> 00:23:00,465
Two desks and one sofa.

395
00:23:01,031 --> 00:23:04,331
Yes, please take them today.

396
00:23:04,498 --> 00:23:05,498
Okay.

397
00:23:18,704 --> 00:23:20,554
Sorry about what happened at the airport.

398
00:23:20,638 --> 00:23:23,071
I'll apologize first.

399
00:23:23,798 --> 00:23:25,164
What are you apologizing for?

400
00:23:26,098 --> 00:23:27,731
Moving out without telling me?

401
00:23:28,331 --> 00:23:29,731
Selling the company behind my back?

402
00:23:30,271 --> 00:23:31,271
Or...

403
00:23:32,098 --> 00:23:34,265
the fake kiss and fake confession?

404
00:23:35,531 --> 00:23:38,131
I have no excuse for any of that.

405
00:23:39,958 --> 00:23:41,858
I'll tell you everything, okay?

406
00:23:42,598 --> 00:23:45,187
Kangsu Construction's CPO
contacted me a while ago.

407
00:23:45,271 --> 00:23:47,404
He said our program was interesting
and wanted to acquire it.

408
00:23:47,488 --> 00:23:50,420
But you wouldn't even let me bring it up.

409
00:23:51,037 --> 00:23:53,837
Even so, how could you toy
with someone's feelings like this?

410
00:23:54,398 --> 00:23:56,098
What did you take me for?

411
00:23:56,204 --> 00:23:57,660
I'm an only son raised by a single mother.

412
00:23:57,744 --> 00:23:59,511
For over five years,

413
00:23:59,565 --> 00:24:01,231
I couldn't even pay for her hospital bills
or living expenses.

414
00:24:01,345 --> 00:24:04,185
I couldn't just stay here with you,

415
00:24:04,217 --> 00:24:06,550
digging this hole with no hope.

416
00:24:06,824 --> 00:24:09,057
Then you should've told me the truth.

417
00:24:09,398 --> 00:24:11,565
How could you stab me in the back
like this?

418
00:24:12,444 --> 00:24:13,444
Give me your account number.

419
00:24:14,131 --> 00:24:15,331
I'll send you half the sale amount.

420
00:24:15,331 --> 00:24:18,162
Let's end this cleanly.

421
00:24:18,246 --> 00:24:20,089
It's a win-win for both of us.

422
00:24:21,057 --> 00:24:22,790
What? A win-win?

423
00:24:24,544 --> 00:24:25,878
How low can you go?

424
00:24:26,525 --> 00:24:28,291
What was I even doing all this time?

425
00:24:29,557 --> 00:24:30,991
This is the best I can do.

426
00:24:31,777 --> 00:24:33,910
Use that money to develop something new.

427
00:24:34,471 --> 00:24:35,805
You're capable!

428
00:24:36,531 --> 00:24:40,331
Don't touch a single cent of that money.
Just think about returning it.

429
00:24:40,858 --> 00:24:43,191
And prepare the penalty if you can.

430
00:24:43,831 --> 00:24:46,331
Return? Penalty?

431
00:24:47,231 --> 00:24:48,231
What do you mean?

432
00:24:48,724 --> 00:24:50,424
It means...

433
00:24:51,331 --> 00:24:53,498
I'm getting my company back. Got that?

434
00:24:56,091 --> 00:24:57,557
Wait.

435
00:24:57,978 --> 00:25:00,334
It was a legal sale.

436
00:25:00,418 --> 00:25:02,418
How are you going to get it back?

437
00:25:04,025 --> 00:25:06,125
Get out. Right now.

438
00:25:07,478 --> 00:25:08,978
The more you act like this,
the more you lose.

439
00:25:09,952 --> 00:25:11,938
Think it over carefully and call me.

440
00:25:12,871 --> 00:25:13,871
Seriously.

441
00:25:15,084 --> 00:25:16,084
I forgot.

442
00:25:16,278 --> 00:25:18,311
I got this cream in Bali.

443
00:25:21,865 --> 00:25:22,865
It's for you.

444
00:25:23,657 --> 00:25:24,924
From Bali?

445
00:25:30,118 --> 00:25:31,298
That's really...

446
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:35,431
That just makes me
want to smack it in your face.

447
00:25:36,158 --> 00:25:37,958
Fix that temper of yours first.

448
00:25:38,578 --> 00:25:40,812
That's why men don't like you.

449
00:25:41,165 --> 00:25:42,798
What did you say?

450
00:25:43,384 --> 00:25:44,351
Get over here.

451
00:25:45,865 --> 00:25:47,531
- Get out!
- Darn it!

452
00:25:48,051 --> 00:25:49,051
Darn it!

453
00:26:01,604 --> 00:26:03,785
(AI friend for seniors,
JOY, bringing people together...)

454
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:04,862
(Lucky Joy Speaker Design)

455
00:26:08,391 --> 00:26:11,391
Strength lies in technology,
but people are stronger.

456
00:26:11,831 --> 00:26:13,965
Cho Eun Ae is even stronger.

457
00:26:23,871 --> 00:26:25,338
I'm not scared.

458
00:26:27,364 --> 00:26:28,598
I'm brave.

459
00:26:30,565 --> 00:26:32,265
I'm not scared.

460
00:26:33,798 --> 00:26:35,131
I'm brave.

461
00:26:47,957 --> 00:26:50,557
I'm not scared. I'm brave.

462
00:26:51,798 --> 00:26:54,831
I'm not scared. I'm brave.

463
00:26:58,131 --> 00:26:59,731
(Kangsu Construction)

464
00:26:59,731 --> 00:27:00,765
A major announcement?

465
00:27:01,704 --> 00:27:04,937
What is it that you're dragging it out
like this?

466
00:27:06,431 --> 00:27:07,731
Just say it.

467
00:27:12,371 --> 00:27:13,405
Ko Dae Chi.

468
00:27:15,831 --> 00:27:16,831
Ko Min Ho.

469
00:27:19,365 --> 00:27:20,365
Ko Gyeol.

470
00:27:21,857 --> 00:27:23,291
Starting today, for the next six months,

471
00:27:24,344 --> 00:27:26,644
you will participate in a race.

472
00:27:27,684 --> 00:27:29,717
A race?

473
00:27:30,671 --> 00:27:33,888
Could you explain that more simply?
What kind of race?

474
00:27:35,437 --> 00:27:39,737
A race to find the next owner
of Kangsu Construction.

475
00:28:06,765 --> 00:28:09,565
(Our Happy Days)

476
00:28:09,891 --> 00:28:11,758
Does this even make sense?

477
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:13,827
Compete in a succession race with Gyeol?

478
00:28:14,065 --> 00:28:16,698
Grandpa, I'll return to where I belong.

479
00:28:16,957 --> 00:28:19,490
This is my last request.

480
00:28:19,824 --> 00:28:22,424
This is my girlfriend, Seo Seung Ri.

481
00:28:22,564 --> 00:28:24,597
Do I look like a joke to you,
Director Ko Min Ho?

482
00:28:24,877 --> 00:28:28,714
It was the CPO who led the acquisition?

483
00:28:28,798 --> 00:28:29,398
(Kangsu Construction)

484
00:28:29,398 --> 00:28:30,898
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
